        <Parent_String>Orycteropus (genus) [300310451], Tubulidentata (order) [300310327], Mammalia (class) [300265707], Vertebrata (subphylum) [300265720], Chordata (phylum) [300266513], Animalia (kingdom) [300249395], Eukaryota (domain) [300265677], living organisms (entities) [300390503], Living Organisms (hierarchy name) [300265673], Agents Facet [300264089]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a species of burrowing nocturnal African edentate mammals having a long snout, long narrow sticky tongue, large ears, a heavy, tapering tail, and long powerful claws for tearing open logs and anthills to feed on ants and termites.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>為一種非洲的夜行性貧齒哺乳類動物，擅挖洞，吻長，舌細長且黏，耳大，尾巴粗重但尾端漸細，爪子長且有力，能夠剖開木頭以及蟻丘，以螞蟻與白蟻為食。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
